INSTRUCTION: SMEMCPY

CATEGORY: Secure Memory Operations

SYNTAX:
SMEMCPY Rdest, Rsrc, Rlen, FLAGS

FLAGS:
- SAFE       (full validation)
- FAST       (reduced checks, still sandboxed)
- ENC        (encrypt destination)
- DEC        (decrypt source)

DESCRIPTION:
Copies memory securely between regions.

EXECUTION:
1. Validate entire memory range before execution
2. Enforce sandbox boundaries
3. Apply encryption/decryption if specified
4. Copy in constant-time blocks
5. Log operation

FAULTS:
- BOUNDS_VIOLATION
- PERMISSION_DENIED

SECURITY:
- Prevents buffer overflow
- Prevents cross-region leaks